- CSS gives style to raw HTML
- CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets
- CSS is used to give style to our web pages
- CSS is used to make website responsive
- HTMLis used to structure a website
- CSS takes responsibility of design
- CSS Syntax SELECTOR{property:value;}
- Selector means where we have to change
- eg:- p{color: blue;}
- We can use group of slectors
- eg- header,p.intro{ background-color:red; border-radius: 3px;}
- Three ways to add CSS to the HTML document
    - Inline CSS: CSS is added to the elements directly using style attribute
    - Internal CSS: CSS is kept inside the head tags in <style> tags
    - External CSS: CSS is kept separately inside a .css stylesheet
    